  "Student B, because their value is higher than the accepted value": "",
  "They have the same percent error since both are 2 degrees off": "",
  "Neither can be calculated because both values are different from 100": "",
  "Student A: |102-100|/100 x 100 = 2%. Student B: |98-100|/100 x 100 = 2%. Both students have the same percent error of 2% because both measurements are exactly 2 degrees away from the accepted value of 100 degrees Celsius.": "",
